snippet.title: Nirvana - "Come As You Are" | Haider Ali (Guitar Cover) #Shorts
snippet.description:
“Come As You Are” by @Nirvana from the album Nevermind — released in 1991 under DGC Records, and produced by Butch Vig at Sound City Studios in Van Nuys, CA, USA — guitar performance by @Haider Ali.

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
I wanted to mix things up a bit so I chose this song as it's pretty simple to play, and quite different from the usual hard rock songs I cover. It was shot and recorded in one take, and I hope you dig it as much as I do, cheers!

snippet.title: Witness Dr. Dawn Hughes Misdiagnosed PTSD — Asked For Cheat Sheet | Defamation Trial Day 14
snippet.description:
Witness Dr. Dawn Hughes Misdiagnosed PTSD — Asked For Cheat Sheet | Defamation Trial Day 14.

Amber Heard's psychologist Dr. Dawn Hughes confirms that she did not administer the gold standard PTSD test known as CAPS-5 on Amber Heard, yet still diagnosed her with PTSD.

Happening in court:
Day 14
Cross Examination of Dr. Dawn Hughes - Forensic Psychologist

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
Actor Johnny Depp is suing ex-wife Amber Heard for $50 million for defamation in connection with Heard’s 2018 Washington Post op-ed, in which she spoke out about being the victim of domestic violence. Heard’s article did not specifically name Depp as her alleged abuser, but according to Depp’s lawsuit, it relied “on the central premise that Ms. Heard was a domestic abuse victim and that Mr. Depp perpetrated domestic violence against her.” Amber Heard is counter-suing Depp for $100 million. 

The defamation trial began Monday in Fairfax County Circuit Court in Virginia, with jury selection completing on the same day. There is a possibility of celebrity witnesses testifying, including James Franco and Elon Musk.

snippet.title: Amber Heard Says Johnny Depp Abandoned Her At Their ENGAGEMENT — Had Drugs | Defamation Trial Day 15
snippet.description:
Amber Heard Says Johnny Depp Abandoned Her At Their ENGAGEMENT — Had Drugs | Defamation Trial Day 15.

Amber Heard accuses Johnny Depp of abandoning her at their engagement party, and that he had drugs with her father David Heard.

Happening in court:
Day 15
Amber Heard - Testifies in Defamation Trial 

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
Actor Johnny Depp is suing ex-wife Amber Heard for $50 million for defamation in connection with Heard’s 2018 Washington Post op-ed, in which she spoke out about being the victim of domestic violence. Heard’s article did not specifically name Depp as her alleged abuser, but according to Depp’s lawsuit, it relied “on the central premise that Ms. Heard was a domestic abuse victim and that Mr. Depp perpetrated domestic violence against her.” Amber Heard is counter-suing Depp for $100 million. 

The defamation trial began Monday in Fairfax County Circuit Court in Virginia, with jury selection completing on the same day. There is a possibility of celebrity witnesses testifying, including James Franco and Elon Musk.

snippet.title: Linkin Park - "Papercut" | Haider Ali (Guitar Cover)
snippet.description:
“Papercut” by @Linkin Park from the album Hybrid Theory — released in 2000 under @Warner Records, and produced by Don Gilmore at NRG Recording Studios in North Hollywood, CA, USA — guitar performance by @Haider Ali.

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
​I believe that @Linkin Park is one of the most quintessential bands of our time, folks. This song came out at the height of their peak — it has a clear message, and now that Chester is no longer with us, it's hard to listen to this song without feeling Chester's pain (may his soul rest in peace). I am dedicating this cover to Chester. Also, I just want to point out that I did record the lead guitar part, but due to time constraints, I couldn't record the video for it. I hope you guys dig it.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Metallica - "Enter Sandman" | Haider Ali (Guitar Cover) #Shorts
snippet.description:
“Enter Sandman” by @Metallica from the album Metallica — released in 1991 under @Elektra Records, and produced by Bob Rock at One on One in Los Angeles, CA, USA 
— guitar performance by @Haider Ali. 

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
Hey folks! In honor of 30 years of @Metallica's landmark record "Metallica/The Black Album," I decided to give a quick tribute by covering one of their most historic song known as "Enter Sandman." I kept it all simple, and gave it a little boost on the low end just to make the sound a bit beefy, and in my humble opinion it works. This record is a personal favorite of mine, and it's truly remarkable, and I still love it to this day. I hope you all enjoy it, folks.

snippet.title: Amber Heard's Lawyer Elaine Bredehoft WARNS Her To STOP Hearsay  — CRAZY | Defamation Trial Day 14
snippet.description:
Amber Heard's Lawyer Elaine Bredehoft WARNS Her To STOP Hearsay  — CRAZY | Defamation Trial Day 14.

Amber Heard's lawyer Elaine Bredehoft warns her to stop hearsay about Lily-Rose Depp, yet she consistently ignores and tells the jury what Johnny Depp's daughter said to her. You have to watch this to believe.

Happening in court:
Day 14
Amber Heard - Testifies in Defamation Trial 

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
Actor Johnny Depp is suing ex-wife Amber Heard for $50 million for defamation in connection with Heard’s 2018 Washington Post op-ed, in which she spoke out about being the victim of domestic violence. Heard’s article did not specifically name Depp as her alleged abuser, but according to Depp’s lawsuit, it relied “on the central premise that Ms. Heard was a domestic abuse victim and that Mr. Depp perpetrated domestic violence against her.” Amber Heard is counter-suing Depp for $100 million. 

The defamation trial began Monday in Fairfax County Circuit Court in Virginia, with jury selection completing on the same day. There is a possibility of celebrity witnesses testifying, including James Franco and Elon Musk.

Amber Heard and her lawyer Elaine Bredehoft can't stop speculation, leading, and hearsay, and make a joke out of themselves with complete lies.

Happening in court:
Day 15
Amber Heard - Testifies in Defamation Trial 

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
Actor Johnny Depp is suing ex-wife Amber Heard for $50 million for defamation in connection with Heard’s 2018 Washington Post op-ed, in which she spoke out about being the victim of domestic violence. Heard’s article did not specifically name Depp as her alleged abuser, but according to Depp’s lawsuit, it relied “on the central premise that Ms. Heard was a domestic abuse victim and that Mr. Depp perpetrated domestic violence against her.” Amber Heard is counter-suing Depp for $100 million. 

The defamation trial began Monday in Fairfax County Circuit Court in Virginia, with jury selection completing on the same day. There is a possibility of celebrity witnesses testifying, including James Franco and Elon Musk.

snippet.title: Three Days Grace - "Animal I Have Become" | Haider Ali (Guitar Cover)
snippet.description:
“Animal I Have Become” by @Three Days Grace from the album One-X — released in 2006 under Jive Records, and produced by Howard Benson at Bay 7 Studios in Calabasas, CA, USA — guitar performance by @Haider Ali.

• Subscribe
https://www.youtube.com/haidertonight?sub_confirmation=1

• Thoughts
Hey, folks, this is the first of many videos to come on my channel, so first and foremost, welcome, and I hope you like what you see here and find it worth your while. This song brings a lot of cool memories from 2006, and I am pretty sure a lot of you will also find this song nostalgic as it was a part of WWE's Smackdown vs Raw (2007) game soundtrack, and it's such a good song with catchy vocal lines, and awesome riffs, so I thought it would be cool to start with this one, and I hope you'll like it as much as I loved playing it, folks. Cheers!
